 "9ed6a296ba50cb886ef304f685ecd1822d997ea4", "parents": ["fbde5320505049a521f2e4f5d535eefb56c25ded"], "tags": []}], "date": 1515800551, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "asasaki@mozilla.com"}, "8535": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1425509 - Initialize PerformanceService in RuntimeService, r=bkelly a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/RuntimeService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "102edbb34a09b8dcfb100ce96d765daa5ace091a", "parents": ["574c337510b15521c16142130a2d1fee407ac25b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kearwood \"Kip\" Gilbert \u003ckgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1426500 - Disable WebVR for macOS on Beta and Release r=daoshengmu a=gchang\n- WebVR will continue to be enabled on macOS for Nightly\n  and Dev Edition\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LpEX13yZVbb", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52f3fbce290687befb442e913faf57763bdf6814", "parents": ["102edbb34a09b8dcfb100ce96d765daa5ace091a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kearwood \"Kip\" Gilbert \u003ckgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1426500 - Part 2: Update test_interfaces mochitest to expect WebVR interfaces to be disabled on release builds for macOS. r=smaug, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/tests/mochitest/general/test_interfaces.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50afadf44520a92711c6e65ff424a300aa0cda4b", "parents": ["52f3fbce290687befb442e913faf57763bdf6814"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1429133 - Some FontExplorer managed fonts are not rendered. r=Alex_Gaynor a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: L5x3GNb3HGU", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicies.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "327ccd0d5dc266b4490d9205da65dee6736bcb9c", "parents": ["50afadf44520a92711c6e65ff424a300aa0cda4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1424341 Add privacy.reduceTimerPrecision and privacy.reduceTimerPrecision.microseconds prefs and tests r=bkelly,timhuang,mrbkap a=gchang\n\nThis pref does not override privacy.resistFingerprinting, but when it is set (and\nprivacy.resistFingerprinting is not) we will still adjust the precision of almost\nall timers. The adjustment amount is the second pref, which is defaulted to\n20us but now dynamically adjustable (in the scale of microseconds.)\n\nWe are landing this preffed off at the current value we clamp performance.now() at\nwhich is 20us.\n\nThis commit is the combination of the multiple commits listed in Bug 1424341", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/browser/browser_performanceAPI.js", "browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/browser/file_workerPerformance.js", "browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/mochitest/file_animation_api.html", "browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/mochitest/test_animation_api.html", "browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/mochitest/test_reduce_time_precision.html", "dom/animation/test/css-transitions/test_animation-starttime.html", "dom/animation/test/document-timeline/test_document-timeline.html", "dom/ipc/ContentPrefs.cpp", "dom/media/test/test_streams_element_capture.html", "dom/media/test/test_streams_element_capture_createObjectURL.html", "dom/media/test/test_video_stats_resistfingerprinting.html", "dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceNavigationTiming.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.h", "modules/libpref/Preferences.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "modules/libpref/test/gtest/CallbackAndVarCacheOrder.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/dom/events/__dir__.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/server-timing/__dir__.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/web-animations/timing-model/animations/__dir__.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/web-animations/timing-model/timelines/__dir__.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/webaudio/the-audio-api/__dir__.ini", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77e197f877508cfcffb11e05252a09f9930b93b1", "parents": ["327ccd0d5dc266b4490d9205da65dee6736bcb9c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1515803162, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8536": {"changesets": [{"author": "Aki Sasaki \u003casasaki@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1430246 - fix beta devedition updates (s,mozilla-aurora,mozilla-beta,). r=jlund a=release CLOSED TREE\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 39QgyKKUUUC", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-final-verify/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-update-verify/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-updates-builder/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f677284ab9bbb7663f3d47f464c43bb98ad0ead", "parents": ["9ed6a296ba50cb886ef304f685ecd1822d997ea4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1515815795, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "asasaki@mozilla.com"}, "8537": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426081 - Migrate legacy search engines to WebExtensions. r=florian a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JfSwJwMC46F", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_migrateWebExtensionEngine.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "912e6c9630a185d5f14388704a11c5e5ac8f2fec", "parents": ["0f677284ab9bbb7663f3d47f464c43bb98ad0ead"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dragana Damjanovic dd.mozilla@gmail.com", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429859 - Check mDoNotTryEarlyData in Do0RTT(). r=mcmanus a=gchang", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6af0590440039c44a5299a8432a0b9f3e1566b13", "parents": ["912e6c9630a185d5f14388704a11c5e5ac8f2fec"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429885 Support a rounding value of 0 for reduceTimerPrecision r=bkelly,timhuang a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F96EUfXgK9F", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "05f9d3f417524ae6a4b8438a3c29b21d014e0da6", "parents": ["6af0590440039c44a5299a8432a0b9f3e1566b13"], "tags": []}], "date": 1516011015, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8538": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 1: DivertComplete should only be sent at OnStopRequest for synthesized responses. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nDiversion for intercepted channels with a synthesized response is a\nspecial case.  It is not appropriate to send DivertComplete when\nmEventQ has been drained, because we are not dealing with the usual\nmEventQ-enqueued OnDataAvailable payloads that had been received over\nthe network and sent down to the child.  In this case, all the data\noriginates in the child and does not go through mEventQ.  As such,\nthe correct place to send DivertComplete is at OnStopComplete for the\nsynthesized response.", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0d0a70391f7357cb48dfdc5814cfbd77be3cabab", "parents": ["77e197f877508cfcffb11e05252a09f9930b93b1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 2: Allow for diversion cancellation and trigger for intercepted channels. r=bkelly, r=mayhemer a=gchang\n\nThe diversion mechanism never expected to be dealing with data sourced\nfrom the content process, but that's exactly what happens with\nServiceWorker-intercepted channels with the current child-intercept\nsituation (which is being fixed).\n\nIn order to allow timely cancellation of diverted intercepted\nchannels, there needs to be a way to relay to the HttpChannelChild\nthat it needs to be canceled so that the synthesized pump can be\ncanceled and diversion can be marked as complete.  This patch adds\nsuch a mechanism to ADivertableParentChannel and PHttpChannel for the\nexclusive use of InterceptedHttpChannel and then uses it.", "files": ["netwerk/base/ADivertableParentChannel.h", "netwerk/protocol/ftp/FTPChannelParent.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/ftp/FTPChannelParent.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/InterceptedHttpChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/InterceptedHttpChannel.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/PHttpChannel.ipdl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a2858960c24e4d855d7fe0560cb406f1b3a8732", "parents": ["0d0a70391f7357cb48dfdc5814cfbd77be3cabab"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 3: (Also Bug 1418795) SyntheticDiversionListener should handle !mIPCOpen. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nThe SyntheticDiversionListener needs to handle the case where the IPC\nconnection is gone.  This patch avoids calling Send* methods which will\ncrash the content process if the actor has already been destroyed.\nAdditionally, OnDataAvailable will return an error in such a case so\nthat the caller can properly handle the error rather than continuing to\nattempt to send data to a listener that doesn't care.  This latter\nchange is an artifact of a previous hack attempt to fix a related\ndiversion issue that is probably not required for this stack, but makes\nsense as a fix, so I've left it in.", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a6d8ac9b23a01b749c5f151df2f80b9e8cf9fde", "parents": ["9a2858960c24e4d855d7fe0560cb406f1b3a8732"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 4: FetchDriver needs to propagate write failures. r=baku a=gchang\n\nIn the scenario where a ServiceWorker returns a pass-through fetch via\n`evt.respondWith(fetch(\"underlying\"))`, in order for the \"underlying\"\nHTTP channel to be canceled when the outer HTTP channel is canceled,\nFetchDriver's OnDataAvailable method needs to return an error when\nthe output pipe experiences an error.\n\nUnfortunately, the contract for ReadSegments is effectively that it\nreturns NS_OK regardless of what the rv of the write handler returned,\nso relying on the returned rv is insufficient.  And because various\nWrite*() methods will all fast-path to returning NS_OK if a count of 0\nis passed, it's necessary to infer a closed/broken pipe by noticing\nthat we tried to write more than 0 bytes of data but 0 bytes were\nwritten.  (This is safe because the pipe we write into was created\nby FetchDriver::OnStartRequest which explicitly creates an infinite\npipe, so it's not possible for the write to fail due to lack of space\nin the pipe.)", "files": ["dom/fetch/FetchDriver.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "20f5dafc5c3bdbd32c9c281b39fb30586c50e37d", "parents": ["3a6d8ac9b23a01b749c5f151df2f80b9e8cf9fde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 5: FetchStreamReader needs to cancel its reader when it encounters write errors. r=baku, f=bkelly a=gchang\n\nCurrently, FetchStreamReader never signals to the JS stream code that\nthe reader has been closed.  This means that when a ServiceWorker\npasses a ReadableStream to respondWith and the HTTP Channel gets\ncanceled, the JS code will keep generating the stream without ever\nrealizing the data's not going anywhere.  It's necessary to cancel\nthe reader.  Or do something like that, this seems to work!", "files": ["dom/fetch/FetchStreamReader.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchStreamReader.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d06c21f21ec73a1b817feeddf6802b9767b68362", "parents": ["20f5dafc5c3bdbd32c9c281b39fb30586c50e37d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 6: Test cancellation of diverted client-intercepted streams. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nThis adds a test where we have a ServiceWorker return 2 different types\nof streams that Firefox recognizes as downloads which are handled by\ndiversion of the channel to the parent.  The diverted downloads are\nthen cancelled and we verify that cancellation actually results in the\nunderlying connections being closed and/or the ServiceWorker notified.\n\nOur 2 types of streams are:\n1. A pass-through stream that is incrementally delivered through use of\n   an .sjs file that delivers data using setInterval.\n2. A SW-authored ReadableStream (which is not enabled by default, so we\n   set a pref.)\n\nDetermining when the .sjs's stream is canceled is accomplished by\nopening a second \"monitor\" connection that only completes when the\nstreaming connection is closed.\n\nIn all cases we differentiate between cancelation and timeouts firing.", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_download_canceled.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/download_canceled/page_download_canceled.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/download_canceled/server-stream-download.sjs", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/download_canceled/sw_download_canceled.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de5ea9bcb2cef9c2bb57de036093197ae3b2a1a1", "parents": ["d06c21f21ec73a1b817feeddf6802b9767b68362"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 0a: Make browser_force_refresh.js clean up after itself. r=bkelly a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_force_refresh.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f9005d863b4aa430aa08bd98c77c3b58c155a7af", "parents": ["de5ea9bcb2cef9c2bb57de036093197ae3b2a1a1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 0b: browser_multie10s_update.js needs to protect its invariants, clean-up after itself. r=bkelly a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_multie10s_update.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcaced69fe4c60d822c669801778f0140330a41e", "parents": ["f9005d863b4aa430aa08bd98c77c3b58c155a7af"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 0c: browser_multie10s_update.js should not use setTimeout. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nThis test used a fixed setTimeout of 3secs for serving the SW.  This\nlower-bounded the test runtime at 6 seconds, plus it was not safe in\nthe event of a slow test runner.\n\nThis set of changes, although a little ugly, improves the logic so that\nthe SW's transmission is driven by a separate \"release\" fetch that is\nonly triggered when both updates have been issued and the first update\nfailure has been reported.  This ensures we are observing the desired\nsituation.  There's also a sanity check on the number of times the SW\nscript is fetched.", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_multie10s_update.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/file_multie10s_update.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/server_multie10s_update.sjs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8668774ec233e58359fb27167ef1a12df4c32b1b", "parents": ["dcaced69fe4c60d822c669801778f0140330a41e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1416879 - Part 0d: Move browser_multie10s_update.js into its own directory. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nThis test is unfortunately a victim of a multi-e10s unregister() race\nfrom browser_force_refresh and given the imminent multi-e10s cleanup\nthat's going to happen, the more complicated alternatives aren't worth\nthe effort versus just moving this test to its own directory.\n\n..and now it's disabled too.  Bug 1429794 tracks re-enabling.", "files": ["dom/workers/moz.build", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_multie10s_update.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/file_multie10s_update.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/isolated/README.md", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/isolated/multi-e10s-update/browser.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/isolated/multi-e10s-update/browser_multie10s_update.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/isolated/multi-e10s-update/file_multie10s_update.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/isolated/multi-e10s-update/server_multie10s_update.sjs", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/server_multie10s_update.sjs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc52af7442696c98d18f5642845d69d16124c732", "parents": ["8668774ec233e58359fb27167ef1a12df4c32b1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1426081 - Migrate legacy search engines to WebExtensions. r=florian a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JfSwJwMC46F", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_migrateWebExtensionEngine.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1485c1f848a7d9e3f661252563b8eca592242b3a", "parents": ["fc52af7442696c98d18f5642845d69d16124c732"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1427221 - Do nsMathMLmfencedFrame cleanup in DestroyFrom, not in the dtor.  r=mattwoodrow a=gchang", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp", "layout/mathml/nsMathMLmfencedFrame.cpp", "layout/mathml/nsMathMLmfencedFrame.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72faa446f04e76ee1fc25dd96cf90ce78be987d9", "parents": ["1485c1f848a7d9e3f661252563b8eca592242b3a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dragana Damjanovic dd.mozilla@gmail.com", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1429859 - Check mDoNotTryEarlyData in Do0RTT(). r=mcmanus a=gchang", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0c5b5676912d96f13661c832bd596c783e933533", "parents": ["72faa446f04e76ee1fc25dd96cf90ce78be987d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1429885 Support a rounding value of 0 for reduceTimerPrecision r=bkelly,timhuang a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F96EUfXgK9F", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff49cdee1a3d4221d20fa7ff554f77ee1b2553f3", "parents": ["0c5b5676912d96f13661c832bd596c783e933533"], "tags": []}], "date": 1516011971, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8539": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 05f9d3f41752 (bug 1429885) because it landed on wrong branch. a=backout", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "faecd3820cf4edcf6f94a329f4ae6962dfb64d49", "parents": ["05f9d3f417524ae6a4b8438a3c29b21d014e0da6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 6af059044003 (bug 1429859) a=backout", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "09bab9dac2557fa568c7072299df0527f073043e", "parents": ["faecd3820cf4edcf6f94a329f4ae6962dfb64d49"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 912e6c9630a1 (bug 1426081) a=backout", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_migrateWebExtensionEngine.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15129163c0eda61d010f114e19f73e11aa61f3fe", "parents": ["09bab9dac2557fa568c7072299df0527f073043e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1516012408, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8540": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1421345 - Check the canary during allocations. r=jet a=gchang", "files": ["xpcom/ds/ArenaAllocator.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e92b07020a5ce08fb5d1b263b38ca438424e1d4", "parents": ["ff49cdee1a3d4221d20fa7ff554f77ee1b2553f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1516016602, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8541": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Backed out changeset 2e92b07020a5 (bug 1421345) for bustage at dist/include/mozilla/ArenaAllocator.h:180:7: 'canary' was not declared in this scope. a=backout", "files": ["xpcom/ds/ArenaAllocator.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9579dad4492b9ce9e2be0379bae320e1f6327394", "parents": ["2e92b07020a5ce08fb5d1b263b38ca438424e1d4"], "tags": ["FENNEC_58_0b17_BUILD1", "FENNEC_58_0b17_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1516017724, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8542": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jason Orendorff \u003cjorendorff@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1426783 - Fix error handling in deserialization of invalid typed arrays. r=sfink, a=gchang.", "files": ["js/src/vm/StructuredClone.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9624359659f033a34985be234cec79efb045bb87", "parents": ["9579dad4492b9ce9e2be0379bae320e1f6327394"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Orendorff \u003cjorendorff@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_58b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1425612 - Better error messages for invalid structured clone data. r=sfink, a=gchang.", "files": ["js/src/vm/StructuredClone.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "db3476b3775994ca22aebbd17854b9a53d2a50b5", "parents": ["9624359659f033a34985be234cec79efb045bb87"], "tags": []}], "date": 1516094587, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8543": {"changesets": [{"author": "Noemi Erli \u003cnerli@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. r=merge a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "ce4d5812e03a48bc5e217b721bea750d43577a33", "parents": ["285a70c630f6003c226dcb68725df137df243ae9", "f7f5ba2214d2ce7b1ce9647b0e2540490a6098a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Myk Melez \u003cmyk@mykzilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429672 - ensure DeferredTask is defined r=jaws\n\nBinding the Preferences object to a \"this\" object was supposed to enable userChangedValue to access the DeferredTask instance that XPCOMUtils.defineLazyModuleGetter defines on the \"this\" object.\n\nI thought that worked, because tests passed, but it turned out that no tests are exercising the branch within userChangedValue that references DeferredTask, which is only followed for pref form controls that specify \"delayprefsave.\"\n\nOnly font controls specify that attribute, and there weren't any tests for changes to those controls.  This patch adds such tests and then changes the way that DeferredTask is lazily retrieved and referenced to ensure it's defined as referenced in userChangedValue.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BPbGp55s9wC", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_basic_rebuild_fonts_test.js", "toolkit/content/preferencesBindings.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72823606d8b47ddbbfa7cb2dd975e0e52f4a60a3", "parents": ["ce4d5812e03a48bc5e217b721bea750d43577a33"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415781 part 1 - Fix test_display_mode tests for local run. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DXysVpV6Lk1", "files": ["layout/style/test/chrome/display_mode_reflow_iframe.html", "layout/style/test/chrome/test_display_mode.html", "layout/style/test/chrome/test_display_mode_reflow.html", "layout/style/test/display_mode_reflow_iframe.html", "layout/style/test/mochitest.ini", "layout/style/test/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa7d09e322e37059b8ace0ffff8a92b00b93b0ff", "parents": ["72823606d8b47ddbbfa7cb2dd975e0e52f4a60a3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415781 part 2 - Make test_display_mode tests wait for the next tick before synthesizing F11 key press. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 12k7zRHw77F", "files": ["layout/style/test/chrome/test_display_mode.html", "layout/style/test/chrome/test_display_mode_reflow.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "09f0935fcc43f257568dc231deb684b3419ecfbf", "parents": ["fa7d09e322e37059b8ace0ffff8a92b00b93b0ff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Silverberg \u003cbsilverberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1390161 - Show that a WebExtension is managing the tracking protection setting, r=jaws,mstriemer\n\nThis adjusts both the new Tracking Protection UI and the old Tracking Protection UI on\nabout:preferences to indicate when an extension is controlling Tracking Protection. It\nwill disable the controls on about:preferences if an extension is in control, and provide\na button to disable the extension.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: G04jWrS6Pr9", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/preferences.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/privacy.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_extension_controlled.js", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/preferences/preferences.properties", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/preferences/privacy.dtd"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "85eb824006694370bcf6cb78aed7aeb11d8ab5d1", "parents": ["09f0935fcc43f257568dc231deb684b3419ecfbf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "cku \u003ccku@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1427109 - Initialize mPrintViaSkPDF as false to guarantee PrintTargetEMF is used only if 'print.print_via_pdf_encoder == skia-pdf'. r=jwatt\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 950x2vDfF17", "files": ["widget/windows/nsDeviceContextSpecWin.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "179d25b3000055ef640f33339745a6c6669ab20a", "parents": ["85eb824006694370bcf6cb78aed7aeb11d8ab5d1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429945 - Make ghost window unlinker e10s compatible. r=smaug\n\nContent processes can contain ghost windows, so the debug-only ghost\nwindow unlinker needs to send a message to child processes to get them\nto run it, too.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9Ffc3SDNDJB", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.h", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/PContent.ipdl", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCComponents.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "117e832dcd6e6e7e5b1a4576d211ec1ccb1a6a47", "parents": ["179d25b3000055ef640f33339745a6c6669ab20a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429954 - Limit docker images retention on try. r=dustin\n\ntaskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/task.py sets an expiry to 28 days for\ntasks on try, vs. 1 year on other projects, but only do that when an\nexpiry is not already set, which docker images do. And they do always\nset to 1 year.\n\nBut it doesn't make sense to keep large docker images from try for a\nyear. So use the same retention policy as the default one. We /could/\njust remove the expiry from docker images and get the task.py default,\nbut it seems like whatever future change might happen to that default\nshouldn't affect docker images, so it's better to duplicate the setting.", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/docker_image.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3453a38c05a3fbcb1935283233d23984d88ea2ef", "parents": ["117e832dcd6e6e7e5b1a4576d211ec1ccb1a6a47"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nevin Chen \u003ccnevinchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1423587 - PWA with expired security certificate should open in browser. r=maliu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1XR3OcP2PpY", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/webapps/WebAppActivity.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07d782c8eb49a26702241461f7144b1741b922da", "parents": ["3453a38c05a3fbcb1935283233d23984d88ea2ef"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429990 - Set display mode back to browser at the end of test_display_mode.html. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LmerI4h1Hld", "files": ["layout/style/test/chrome/test_display_mode.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f05450f256c8a9006a8473b3bee5bde214890e7", "parents": ["07d782c8eb49a26702241461f7144b1741b922da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424113 - remove CPOWs objects from autoplay tests. r=dao\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EJCTfie0cH8", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_play_twice.js", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_user_gestures.js", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/file_video.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9517df1f4b1b7be45c6ffce4c6123e917fb2acf5", "parents": ["9f05450f256c8a9006a8473b3bee5bde214890e7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429721 - Ensure all netmonitor columns have a default width. r=rickychien\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DsjNMlMptPL", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/assets/styles/RequestList.css", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/constants.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_pref.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_showhide.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_headers-alignment.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "76d24a5414eb18d4c3b98fe56e3009e14589d857", "parents": ["9517df1f4b1b7be45c6ffce4c6123e917fb2acf5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429979 Part 1 - Use LookupForAdd() to avoid explicit new nsAutoPtr. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2LaQVRhPGPB", "files": ["layout/style/ImageLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5fc44817e8338df6fef166e0707e4fc5824353d0", "parents": ["76d24a5414eb18d4c3b98fe56e3009e14589d857"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429979 Part 2 - Use ranged-based for loop to iterate FrameSet. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: I1aP3Kpqebf", "files": ["layout/style/ImageLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0cef7b376e37af3c31efce8323fd3aa52e710c1b", "parents": ["5fc44817e8338df6fef166e0707e4fc5824353d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429979 Part 3 - Use nsClassHashtable::Get() which directly returns the value. r=heycam\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7yVbVxMqEde", "files": ["layout/style/ImageLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a9f600f565806c895708e43ffda1baa8d5888fc", "parents": ["0cef7b376e37af3c31efce8323fd3aa52e710c1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Towkir Ahmed \u003ctowkir17@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399897 - Restrict the height of console table and add sticky headers; r=nchevobbe\n\nSince table elements (th, tr) do not support sticky headers, the console table now\nuses only sibling divs for the cells, with appropriate aria attributes and a CSS grid\nto mimic an actual table.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J8hmy7H4GKL", "files": ["devtools/client/themes/webconsole.css", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/components/ConsoleTable.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "914fce4a03e31172958705299a83128633911d48", "parents": ["4a9f600f565806c895708e43ffda1baa8d5888fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1399897 - Fix console_table mochitest; r=Honza.\n\nNow that we are using sibling divs for all the cells of the table,\nwe don't have the same notion of what is a row.\nThe console table test is adapted to the new component.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HcfzTaRVIcN", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_console_table.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83acad9bf47b7c32947d37f03e60622722c1fd88", "parents": ["914fce4a03e31172958705299a83128633911d48"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429021 - Don't try to start DBus service without any application/profile name, r=jhorak\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 97jawSNNp3i", "files": ["toolkit/components/remote/nsDBusRemoteService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed6f1ea151c1eb56e2d45da039e7694bce70f32a", "parents": ["83acad9bf47b7c32947d37f03e60622722c1fd88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Narcis Beleuzu \u003cnbeleuzu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 76d24a5414eb (bug 1429721) for devtools failure on browser_net_headers-alignment.js. on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/assets/styles/RequestList.css", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/constants.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_pref.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_showhide.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_headers-alignment.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74e94759584cda78f2c715bbb8a5c3ab1c524e37", "parents": ["ed6f1ea151c1eb56e2d45da039e7694bce70f32a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418425 - Compile zlib as host lib r=glandium\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5jXyVhRI0kD", "files": ["modules/zlib/src/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "218077e821156a9b9c03eb1e70740558284ad1d0", "parents": ["74e94759584cda78f2c715bbb8a5c3ab1c524e37"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418425 - Update bsdiff to use libz instead of bz2 for the crc algo r=glandium\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2GLmnzF9CMh", "files": ["other-licenses/bsdiff/bsdiff.c", "other-licenses/bsdiff/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "29fd023f999f94365889414c9e968a0f7538b151", "parents": ["218077e821156a9b9c03eb1e70740558284ad1d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418425 - Ship only the crc table from bz2 and use it in the updater r=glandium\n\nIndeed, using zlib gives different results which mismatch with the one from\nreleng.\n\nThe next step would be to have releng use a zlib based solution.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LwxHk84Ajp4", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/archivereader.cpp", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/crctable.h", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/moz.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater-common.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater-xpcshell/moz.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "772538a846cb867352b46d3d282ed4a4ee301f33", "parents": ["29fd023f999f94365889414c9e968a0f7538b151"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418425 - Remove libbz2 files as we were only using it for crc32 as the updater moved to lzma r=glandium\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8Sz8vtV0b5G", "files": ["config/external/moz.build", "config/system-headers.mozbuild", "modules/libbz2/moz.build", "modules/libbz2/src/LICENSE", "modules/libbz2/src/blocksort.c", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib.c", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib.h", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib_private.h", "modules/libbz2/src/compress.c", "modules/libbz2/src/crctable.c", "modules/libbz2/src/decompress.c", "modules/libbz2/src/huffman.c", "modules/libbz2/src/moz.build", "modules/libbz2/src/randtable.c", "old-configure.in", "tools/rewriting/ThirdPartyPaths.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d32ae48690a7e62946a6a8ad1e925ffbcbae253f", "parents": ["772538a846cb867352b46d3d282ed4a4ee301f33"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418425 - Do not build bsdiff on Android. The updater doesn't use it (we ship apk directly) r=glandium\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FZ7A05WsQjO", "files": ["toolkit/toolkit.mozbuild"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8154486d3e00cadfe9f22178dd0737817a0c9555", "parents": ["d32ae48690a7e62946a6a8ad1e925ffbcbae253f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429721 - Ensure all netmonitor columns have a default width. r=rickychien\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9cOzW155yaf", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/assets/styles/RequestList.css", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/constants.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_pref.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_columns_showhide.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_headers-alignment.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1fc038162868151da0d94f6cb29d7a8e5a0651a6", "parents": ["8154486d3e00cadfe9f22178dd0737817a0c9555"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ricky Chien \u003cricky060709@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1409705 - Adding Cu.isDeadWrapper(window) to avoid accessing dead object r=Honza\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1Qpb6p2Jwnz", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/tab.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b29651a367a0ff830bc64800752a3a6caffa484", "parents": ["1fc038162868151da0d94f6cb29d7a8e5a0651a6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429701 - Enable ESLint rule mozilla/use-services for dom/indexedDB. r=bevis\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9OgcN56ziip", "files": [".eslintrc.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/bug839193.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/head.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/helpers.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/test_filehandle_lifetimes_nested.html", "dom/indexedDB/test/test_filehandle_success_events_after_abort.html", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_bad_origin_directory.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_globalObjects_other.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_idle_maintenance.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_metadata2Restore.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_metadataRestore.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_oldDirectories.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_open_for_principal.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_open_objectStore.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_success_events_after_abort.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/test_transaction_lifetimes_nested.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/xpcshell-head-child-process.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/unit/xpcshell-head-parent-process.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "698ae46fa6340bfc93f5e9f212391bf8bc6feaa5", "parents": ["8b29651a367a0ff830bc64800752a3a6caffa484"], "tags": []}, {"author": "rohan \u003crohan17089@iiitd.ac.in\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1422035 - Make RegisterEvents assert on children processes. r=Dexter\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AnItcTFejUH", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEvent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "686aaeae4c9239c508f561669a2766b8f9a02d4a", "parents": ["698ae46fa6340bfc93f5e9f212391bf8bc6feaa5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Narcis Beleuzu \u003cnbeleuzu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 5 changesets (bug 1418425) for windows build bustage \"mbsdiff.exe : fatal error LNK1120\". on a CLOSED TREE\n\nBacked out changeset 8154486d3e00 (bug 1418425)\nBacked out changeset d32ae48690a7 (bug 1418425)\nBacked out changeset 772538a846cb (bug 1418425)\nBacked out changeset 29fd023f999f (bug 1418425)\nBacked out changeset 218077e82115 (bug 1418425)", "files": ["config/external/moz.build", "config/system-headers.mozbuild", "modules/libbz2/moz.build", "modules/libbz2/src/LICENSE", "modules/libbz2/src/blocksort.c", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib.c", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib.h", "modules/libbz2/src/bzlib_private.h", "modules/libbz2/src/compress.c", "modules/libbz2/src/crctable.c", "modules/libbz2/src/decompress.c", "modules/libbz2/src/huffman.c", "modules/libbz2/src/moz.build", "modules/libbz2/src/randtable.c", "modules/zlib/src/moz.build", "old-configure.in", "other-licenses/bsdiff/bsdiff.c", "other-licenses/bsdiff/moz.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/archivereader.cpp", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/crctable.h", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/moz.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater-common.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater-xpcshell/moz.build", "toolkit/mozapps/update/updater/updater.cpp", "toolkit/toolkit.mozbuild", "tools/rewriting/ThirdPartyPaths.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c011bb60725113e3da91a813b8ef250cf2109b3d", "parents": ["686aaeae4c9239c508f561669a2766b8f9a02d4a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Consider \u003coptgroup\u003e when finding container element. r=automatedtester\n\nIt is a bug in element.getContainer that \u003coptgroup\u003e is not considered\nwhen locating the containing context element, \u003cselect\u003e.  \u003coptgroup\u003e\nis also a child element of \u003cselect\u003e on the same level as \u003coption\u003e.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2GJJrRuY5Th", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4bf05eb6e9b6ab20685a8edf625a3c946c409ee9", "parents": ["c011bb60725113e3da91a813b8ef250cf2109b3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Add shorthand for emulating DOM blur event. r=automatedtester\n\nAs part of the focussing steps we subsequently need to blur the\nelement after a focus.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: xyCcmqeOpO", "files": ["testing/marionette/event.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4cdb2c2eb4c4739b8d54843d30b09f11418da38e", "parents": ["4bf05eb6e9b6ab20685a8edf625a3c946c409ee9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Add element.findClosest for finding ancestor by CSS selector. r=automatedtester\n\nIntroduces a new function, element.findClosest, that finds the\nclosest parent node by a CSS selector expression.  This is useful to\nfind arbitrary elements in the tree above us and is quite possibly\nreusable for element.getContainer.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8rBEepmDdPm", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/test_element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9350c2e8e01f8ed1e3fb6f88e291264fa0f68bdb", "parents": ["4cdb2c2eb4c4739b8d54843d30b09f11418da38e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Use element.findClosest in element.getContainer. r=automatedtester\n\nelement.findClosest is a more generalised version of findAncestralElement,\nwhich is limited to a list of element tag names.  By using\nelement.findClosest and CSS matching we also avoid a redundant iteration.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 32QwmkwiGf5", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1c2ba38f6989bc548a970687a43dc7675aec2791", "parents": ["9350c2e8e01f8ed1e3fb6f88e291264fa0f68bdb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Add element.isReadOnly. r=automatedtester\n\nIntroduces new function for testing whether an element is read-only.\nThis content IDL attribute only applies to \u003cinput\u003e and \u003ctextarea\u003e\nelements.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1YLizKUYMU6", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/test_element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65547df5268495dac490a219679755df75564887", "parents": ["1c2ba38f6989bc548a970687a43dc7675aec2791"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Add element.isDisabled. r=automatedtester\n\nAdds a new function called element.isDisabled to test for disabledness.\nAn element is only considered disabled if it is indeed an element\nthat can be disabled, for example that it is a \u003cbutton\u003e, \u003cinput\u003e,\n\u003cselect\u003e, \u003ctextarea\u003e, \u003coptgroup\u003e, or \u003coption\u003e element.  All other\nelements are not disabled.\n\nIn nested trees the disabledness state of a containing element\naffects child elements, without this being refelected in the child\nelement's content IDL attribute.  In the following example, the\n\u003coption\u003e element is disabled:\n\n\t\u003cselect disabled\u003e\n\t  \u003coption\u003efoo\n\t\u003c/select\u003e\n\nSimilarly:\n\n\t\u003cselect\u003e\n\t\t\u003coptgroup disabled\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003coption\u003ebar\n\t\t\u003c/optgroup\u003e\n\t\u003c/select\u003e\n\nThis means we have to traverse the tree to find the closest ancestral\nparent element, whether it is \u003coptgroup\u003e or \u003cselect\u003e, and inspect\nits state before we can be sure the element in question is not disabled.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 578zLNj7nXK", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/test_element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "81c470ac944a856185fe683bc2f8da391cbcd27c", "parents": ["65547df5268495dac490a219679755df75564887"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Add element.isEditingHost and element.isEditable. r=automatedtester\n\nIntroduces two new functions called element.isEditingHost, for\ndetermining if an element is content-editable or part of a document\nin design mode, and element.isEditable, which implements the\nWebDriver-defined concept of what it means for an element to be editable.\n\nWebDriver consideres an element editable if it is not read-only or\ndisabled, and one of the following conditions are met:\n\n  - It is a \u003ctextarea\u003e element.\n\n  - It is an element that is not of the checkbox, radio, hidden,\n    submit, button, or image types.\n\n  - It is content-editable.\n\n  - It belongs to a document in design mode.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6U71uSUNwoI", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/test_element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "66f58d8f33559bf9b1f8206a857312641ee1b169", "parents": ["81c470ac944a856185fe683bc2f8da391cbcd27c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Make WebDriver:ElementClear conforming to standard. r=automatedtester\n\nThis implements the remote end steps for the Element Clear command\nfrom WebDriver in Marionette.\n\nThe WPT test webdriver/tests/interaction/element_clear.py was deleted\nbecause it tested a previous definition of the Element Clear command\nand many of its tests were either incorrect or replaced by the new tests.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: C2xmIlhSAdW", "files": ["testing/marionette/interaction.js", "testing/marionette/listener.js", "testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/interaction/element_clear.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f9f835bce31b7a0f40c2a8e69b83cf8aaf4b4024", "parents": ["66f58d8f33559bf9b1f8206a857312641ee1b169"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Remove clearElement atom. r=automatedtester\n\nThe previous patch in this changeset made us independent from the\nSelenium clearElement atom.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DejxgD9t9Go", "files": ["testing/marionette/atom.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ab0d72e5e0bdb73f6d0c88a563b2720d839bc5b", "parents": ["f9f835bce31b7a0f40c2a8e69b83cf8aaf4b4024"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354211 - Remove Mn test for WebDriver:ElementClear. r=automatedtester\n\nThis test passes after switching to the WebDriver conforming\nimplementation of the Element Clear command, but in an effort to\nmove us off proprietary Mn tests this patch removes the old tests.\n\nThe new WPT tests introduces as part of this changeset are considered\nfunctionally equivalent or better.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8XqhnmCctoX", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_clearing.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/unit-tests.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15b42d200275ca628c605366f45b13711333f558", "parents": ["9ab0d72e5e0bdb73f6d0c88a563b2720d839bc5b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429709 - make relative SVG links absolute, r=jaws\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9kSdFbpPx32", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_contextmenu.js", "browser/base/content/test/general/subtst_contextmenu.html", "browser/modules/ContextMenu.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e50d4cdb9fa7b19f8e2643c968ca89d9902b9f8d", "parents": ["15b42d200275ca628c605366f45b13711333f558"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430009 - Remove reference to externalToolbars in customizableui toolbar.xml binding. r=Gijs\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CMKNn7jdcVq", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/content/toolbar.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c11b6d76a5acbb81510bb29f36b2d47411917a7b", "parents": ["e50d4cdb9fa7b19f8e2643c968ca89d9902b9f8d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland r=merge a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/browser_multie10s_update.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/file_multie10s_update.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/server_multie10s_update.sjs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "2ca9f26c449c5324a50a695209feacbc4e73a274", "parents": ["c11b6d76a5acbb81510bb29f36b2d47411917a7b", "d2edd256c3aadb1cea48da0c8f62f725bd53cb76"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miko Mynttinen \u003cmikokm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428906 - Implement Clone() and copy-constructors for nsDisplayTableBlendMode, nsDisplayTableBlendContainer, and nsDisplayTableFixedPosition r=mattwoodrow\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Fr34xFp4n8", "files": ["layout/painting/crashtests/1428906-1.html", "layout/painting/crashtests/crashtests.list", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec9db833ef5b932c483b03f0e3b0cd6632f0f663", "parents": ["2ca9f26c449c5324a50a695209feacbc4e73a274"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug: Remove some unused functions. r=me\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3sUI1K0dIeA\n", "files": ["js/src/devtools/rootAnalysis/analyzeHeapWrites.js", "layout/style/ServoBindings.cpp", "layout/style/ServoBindings.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "822e3896efed8822e5c2776e7a5873bce63f3e2e", "parents": ["ec9db833ef5b932c483b03f0e3b0cd6632f0f663"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19747 - style: Add a document state invalidator (from emilio:doc-state-invalidator); r=upsuper\n\nDon't use it yet (since I was working from a Servo tree). Will hook it up and improve in the Gecko bug.\n\nRight now it takes a `StyleRuleCascadeData`, which means that if all the origins in the document have state selectors we could do just one walk over the tree and not multiple, that will be improved.\n\nOther than that, this is completely untested of course, but I prefer to land it, given I don't think it's complex, and work on the Gecko integration separately. The reason for this is that I also plan to fix the `\u003cslot\u003e` bugs, which will change `StyleRuleCascadeData` and such, and I want the two bugs to conflict as little as possible.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 50e4171958d4ff7f1c76d133a8f89e7d5995376f", "files": ["servo/components/selectors/context.rs", "servo/components/selectors/parser.rs", "servo/components/selectors/size_of_tests.rs", "servo/components/style/data.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/selector_parser.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/wrapper.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/document_state.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/invalidation_map.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/invalidator.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/state_and_attributes.rs", "servo/components/style/servo/selector_parser.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d80a7ef3d32b3ca1e9dfaf0803c61e752261a4d7", "parents": ["822e3896efed8822e5c2776e7a5873bce63f3e2e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430036 - Don't set PKG_CONFIG_LIBDIR when building on Debian. r=ted", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/linux32/debug-asan", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux32/nightly-asan", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/debug-asan", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/debug-searchfox-clang", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/debug-static-analysis-clang", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/hazards", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/nightly-asan", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/nightly-asan-reporter", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/nightly-fuzzing-asan", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/opt-static-analysis-clang", "browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/opt-tsan", "build/unix/mozconfig.linux", "build/unix/mozconfig.linux32"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd2dd542895fa0332959c7a877a2d71a4c6c0ef2", "parents": ["d80a7ef3d32b3ca1e9dfaf0803c61e752261a4d7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1427471 - Set app.update.enabled to false when building with --disable-updater. r=rhelmer", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54e562a94c3cf3da45af5a72bb8c81b5ef5a609f", "parents": ["cd2dd542895fa0332959c7a877a2d71a4c6c0ef2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kingston \u003cjkt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398169 - Use pref to disable registerContentHandler in non stable builds. r=baku,dao\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Gbo1wFr8XU6", "files": ["browser/components/feeds/test/mochitest.ini", "browser/components/feeds/test/test_registerHandler.html", "browser/components/feeds/test/test_registerHandler_disabled.html", "dom/webidl/Navigator.webidl", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/webappapis/system-state-and-capabilities/the-navigator-object/historical.window.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "189a02700a27311b5a62def8fa27e1aabd5eca4f", "parents": ["54e562a94c3cf3da45af5a72bb8c81b5ef5a609f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1416041 - Collapse one-offs buttons if only the current engine is active and don't select search settings when collapsed. r=florian\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9aOM19NPRzt", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_urlbarOneOffs.js", "browser/components/search/content/search.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "69408f067a9ccde6041ca26449eae32a4011499b", "parents": ["189a02700a27311b5a62def8fa27e1aabd5eca4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426081 - Migrate legacy search engines to WebExtensions. r=florian\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JfSwJwMC46F", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_migrateWebExtensionEngine.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a3e930a4edfd0a1913cfa7d41ee59a0e0aa79ea8", "parents": ["69408f067a9ccde6041ca26449eae32a4011499b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430128 - Remove remnants of the iconsize attribute. r=Gijs\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3a80XcR3NUM", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.xul", "browser/components/customizableui/content/toolbar.xml", "browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/toolbar.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "186c8d28a01b57bfb8d1af2cd47029290802180c", "parents": ["a3e930a4edfd0a1913cfa7d41ee59a0e0aa79ea8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Glenn Watson \u003cgithub@intuitionlibrary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19750 - Update WR (new transaction API) (from glennw:update-wr-api); r=jdm\n\nIn the future we'll want to start making use of this in Servo\nto get atomic updates of resources with display list changes etc.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 75f39b42abc88a2597186fe845d2deaa15bdb6da", "files": ["servo/Cargo.lock"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eb8b800a2c8b0d221b6a22a236b4ec5c6c82fcdf", "parents": ["186c8d28a01b57bfb8d1af2cd47029290802180c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Revert \"Bug 1363725 - Change inconsistent occurrence of 'all_child', 'all_childs' to 'all_children' and 'AllChilds' to 'AllChildren' in code and docs.\" r=Dexter\n\nThis reverts commit c238437964d1bfedd389ae72fd0da0f5f119211a.\n\nIt caused upstream processing headaches. We'll need to address those before\nrelanding.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Ae2d8iMPQuz", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryCommon.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryCommon.h", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/events.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/histograms.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/scalars.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/shared_telemetry_utils.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f345451c208356279254fdf5efa95fbad83abcbd", "parents": ["eb8b800a2c8b0d221b6a22a236b4ec5c6c82fcdf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 586838 - Add NEON versions of LossyConvertEncoding. r=erahm", "files": ["xpcom/string/moz.build", "xpcom/string/nsUTF8Utils.h", "xpcom/string/nsUTF8UtilsNEON.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3db5dd3a6fe64dd31129fdaa2e2015b93801c675", "parents": ["3776f91840a4c641317b4719332a5103e317f6bb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426087: Decrement nsDocumentViewer::mDestroyRefCount in a separate function. r=jwatt", "files": ["layout/base/nsDocumentViewer.cpp", "layout/base/nsIDocumentViewerPrint.h", "layout/printing/nsPagePrintTimer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86d41b5efe074f6988085082df9ef537eee0813a", "parents": ["3db5dd3a6fe64dd31129fdaa2e2015b93801c675"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kai Engert \u003ckaie@kuix.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1420060, NSS_3_35_BETA1, r=franziskus\nUPGRADE_NSS_RELEASE", "files": ["security/nss/TAG-INFO", "security/nss/automation/clang-format/setup.sh", "security/nss/automation/taskcluster/docker-clang-3.9/setup.sh", "security/nss/automation/taskcluster/docker-hacl/setup.sh", "security/nss/automation/taskcluster/docker/setup.sh", "security/nss/automation/taskcluster/graph/src/extend.js", "security/nss/automation/taskcluster/graph/src/try_syntax.js", "security/nss/cmd/certutil/certutil.c", "security/nss/coreconf/config.gypi", "security/nss/coreconf/coreconf.dep", "security/nss/gtests/freebl_gtest/rsa_unittest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/softoken_gtest/softoken_gtest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/ssl_agent_unittest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/ssl_custext_unittest.cc", "security/nss/lib/ckfw/builtins/certdata.txt", "security/nss/lib/ckfw/builtins/nssckbi.h", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/seckey.c", "security/nss/lib/softoken/fipstokn.c", "security/nss/lib/softoken/pkcs11.c", "security/nss/lib/softoken/pkcs11i.h", "security/nss/lib/softoken/sdb.c", "security/nss/lib/softoken/sdb.h", "security/nss/lib/softoken/sftkdb.c", "security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3prot.h", "security/nss/lib/ssl/sslt.h", "security/nss/lib/ssl/tls13con.c", "security/nss/lib/util/nssutil.def", "security/nss/lib/util/utilmod.c", "security/nss/lib/util/utilpars.c", "security/nss/lib/util/utilpars.h", "security/nss/lib/util/utilparst.h", "security/nss/readme.md", "security/nss/tests/all.sh", "security/nss/tests/cert/TestCA-bogus-rsa-pss1.crt", "security/nss/tests/cert/TestCA-bogus-rsa-pss2.crt", "security/nss/tests/cert/cert.sh", "security/nss/tests/fips/fips.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "92dcb99abd054bd9a502ae3b9da2af983d137aad", "parents": ["86d41b5efe074f6988085082df9ef537eee0813a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kai Engert \u003ckaie@kuix.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1420060, export new NSS APIs in Firefox' specific API export list, r=franziskus", "files": ["security/nss.symbols"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ddfff454c810d25532d60ca8a60f0d7a86edb1f8", "parents": ["92dcb99abd054bd9a502ae3b9da2af983d137aad"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kai Engert \u003ckaie@kuix.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1420060, restrict export of symbols to Windows, suggested by Masatoshi Kimura, r=kaie", "files": ["security/nss.symbols"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35dcf8417877e6cfe7dda378a1c2f3682c3c3af1", "parents": ["ddfff454c810d25532d60ca8a60f0d7a86edb1f8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masatoshi Kimura \u003cVYV03354@nifty.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428538 - Use UTF-8 file paths for NSS database. r=keeler", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsNSSComponent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95e2f1556c172a88792415f3a5637f9cbcac2358", "parents": ["35dcf8417877e6cfe7dda378a1c2f3682c3c3af1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Adrian Wielgosik \u003cadrian.wielgosik@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1361815 - Do less work in nsTArray's Clear() and destructor. r=froydnj\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DnkE7LFxkF3\n", "files": ["xpcom/ds/nsTArray.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd2b9748cbb66622643d5a15a2efe6edd8707ff1", "parents": ["95e2f1556c172a88792415f3a5637f9cbcac2358"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429088: Crashtest. r=bz\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: qJQdpdUROs\n", "files": ["layout/base/crashtests/1429088.html", "layout/base/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e013d41a44e7b9178d155571d18e329128191499", "parents": ["dd2b9748cbb66622643d5a15a2efe6edd8707ff1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428515 - Check for dying JSObjects when accessing plugin wrapper table r=bz\n\nThe sNPObjWrappers table can contain entries for dead JSObjects that have not yet been finalised.  We need to take care not to trigger mJSObj's read barrier for such entries since that will attempt to expose the object to JS and cause this assertion.\n\nThe patch does this by calling unbarrieredGetPtr() which avoids the barrier.\n\nNote converting a TenuredHeap to bool and testing equality against a pointer don't trigger the barrier.", "files": ["dom/plugins/base/nsJSNPRuntime.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d119babafa27f8dd5a4af2b0d418029006a5794b", "parents": ["e013d41a44e7b9178d155571d18e329128191499"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429783 - Reset frozen state in nsIScriptElement::LoseParserInsertedness() r=smaug", "files": ["dom/html/crashtests/1429783.html", "dom/script/nsIScriptElement.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "019f0d0bd98d17b27bedb52068f4b36efd805b5c", "parents": ["d119babafa27f8dd5a4af2b0d418029006a5794b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paolo Amadini \u003cpaolo.mozmail@amadzone.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1284391 - Remove ui.allow_platform_file_picker pref on GTK widget. r=karlt\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Gdiww1Gbwpk", "files": ["browser/installer/package-manifest.in", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "toolkit/components/filepicker/content/filepicker.js", "toolkit/components/filepicker/content/filepicker.xul", "toolkit/components/filepicker/jar.mn", "toolkit/components/filepicker/moz.build", "toolkit/components/filepicker/nsFilePicker.js", "toolkit/components/filepicker/nsFilePicker.manifest", "toolkit/components/filepicker/nsFileView.cpp", "toolkit/components/filepicker/nsIFileView.idl", "toolkit/components/filepicker/test/unit/.eslintrc.js", "toolkit/components/filepicker/test/unit/test_filecomplete.js", "toolkit/components/filepicker/test/unit/xpcshell.ini", "toolkit/components/moz.build", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/filepicker.dtd", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/filepicker.properties", "toolkit/locales/jar.mn", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/filepicker.css", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/filepicker/Filepicker.png", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/jar.mn", "widget/gtk/nsWidgetFactory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b8a5f9aac6fb43dc84a9a135084ee