ish", "files": ["dom/media/CubebUtils.cpp", "dom/media/CubebUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b41fbd6b35ab6490ea888e36950c28ea7e4f7b5", "parents": ["9e0486fd4eec7b25381f97c16d122246b3772453"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gregan \u003ckinetik@flim.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426867 - Init AudioIPC even earlier.  r=kamidphish", "files": ["dom/media/CubebUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14b5945f84c42131e13832d09075f76778ce4505", "parents": ["7b41fbd6b35ab6490ea888e36950c28ea7e4f7b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gregan \u003ckinetik@flim.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430870 - Avoid static ctors in AudioIPC startup code.  r=kamidphish", "files": ["dom/media/CubebUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c33945be1657a720fc1ec79124e0e85df0dffeaa", "parents": ["14b5945f84c42131e13832d09075f76778ce4505"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bevis Tseng \u003cbtseng@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428253 - Resume the test at next tick after the resolve of openTabSelectedPromise. r=:Gijs.\n\nWith the conformant promising scheduling, the promise callback can be performed\neariler at the returning from a event listener if possible instead of the end\nof current task.\n\nThe resolving of \"selected\" change of the openedTab becomes part of the process\nof RemotePrompt.openTabPrompt() where the 'DOMWillOpenModalDialog' event is fired.\n\nWe should resume the test at next tick to ensure that the openTabPrompt() is\ndone before removing the openedTab.", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/tabPrompts/browser_openPromptInBackgroundTab.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37c38f403e4d34de41a568136e7b7fb45dd38fb5", "parents": ["c33945be1657a720fc1ec79124e0e85df0dffeaa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gregan \u003ckinetik@flim.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425788 - Disable AudioIPC on macOS while investigating fa