], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426244 - Follow-up to use notimestamp; r=me\n\nAdd a notimestamp option to not add timestamps to javadoc.", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/build.gradle"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a98033301da83cdac1015bde1c7d3627aa0dab9", "parents": ["8aa90bdddd800dba6ad5ad2718ce32b0e6c3e761"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Pradeep \u003cpradeepgangwar39@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1406383- Add documentation for squashing commits; r=sole DONTBUILD\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 82TOmqxtDkE\n***\nBug 1406383- Add documentation for squashing commits; r=sole", "files": ["devtools/docs/contributing/making-prs.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "128fc731770c4a8890623ea693f6dda7dcf23309", "parents": ["3a98033301da83cdac1015bde1c7d3627aa0dab9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1417446 - Remove MESSAGE_ADD action;r=bgrins.\n\nThis action is not used anywhere since we batch messages and thus use MESSAGES_ADD action.\nThe tests that were using it now use messagesAdd.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9DvyrpR4ocC", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/actions/messages.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/constants.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/reducers/messages.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/store.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/store/release-actors.test.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/store/ui.test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fccc4ee24bd6a2ee6c5cd827bb213d365f3c0069", "parents": ["514350cead8b3369ab9e50caafcbb21827e91ff9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike de Boer \u003cmdeboer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429490 - Since nsISerializationHelper.serializeToString may throw, catch the error to prevent loss of session data. r=ckerschb\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GOAFT4CpVrR", "files": ["toolkit/modules/sessionstore/Utils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "923f5a36fa8d340a87a3fc968cd55782254b6997", "parents": ["fccc4ee24bd6a2ee6c5cd827bb213d365f3c0069"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1423200 - When setting up a new content viewer, if the previous PresShell was active, make the new one active too. r=mystor\n\nIt's possible to RenderLayers for a top-level content process DocShell without that DocShell being\nactive. When we do this, the PresShell for that DocShell becomes active, but the DocShell stays\ninactive (to avoid accidentally playing paused video or clearing notifications in that DocShell).\n\nIf a DocShell is inactive but rendering its layers, it's possible for that DocShell to navigate.\nWhen this occurs, a new PresShell can be created, which normally reads its active state off of\nthe DocShell. This means that the PresShell will become inactive even though the tab is supposed\nto continue rendering its layers.\n\nThis patch checks for PresShell active state when setting up a new content viewer after a navigation,\nand if the previous PresShell was active, makes the new PresShell active too.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KX9HvZJKqg2", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1765a455cc35fb3d3ccb7f2e3004bbacc7448105", "parents": ["923f5a36fa8d340a87a3fc968cd55782254b6997"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott Wu \u003cscottcwwu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1419312 - Expand supported locales and countries on Nightly and Beta. r=lchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8MziULBn05l", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/bootstrap.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1b36b7371595f88f2de56f1760d7088896f2a4e3", "parents": ["1765a455cc35fb3d3ccb7f