esc": "No bug - Tagging daeb05a6586b5c3ec5b7c4ba1a980f50e3620937 with FIREFOX_59_0b11_BUILD1, FIREFOX_59_0b11_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "992102c7b304a6f45b5d78fafbef064e41b032c3", "parents": ["57794dfccbc998ab03dc543231d17959b8c606e5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519144834, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8738": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging daeb05a6586b5c3ec5b7c4ba1a980f50e3620937 with DEVEDITION_59_0b11_BUILD1, DEVEDITION_59_0b11_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07e5563515380b38c110c1cd7c4be9a4c017af1e", "parents": ["992102c7b304a6f45b5d78fafbef064e41b032c3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519144986, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8739": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging daeb05a6586b5c3ec5b7c4ba1a980f50e3620937 with FENNEC_59_0b11_BUILD1, FENNEC_59_0b11_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "04ec73c33ff12871343c7fe5dad3cc58c428a30a", "parents": ["07e5563515380b38c110c1cd7c4be9a4c017af1e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519162418, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8740": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1432409 part 1 - Prevent nsDeviceContextSpecProxy using RemotePrintJobChild if initialization fails. r=dholbert, a=lizzard\n\nWhen RemotePrintJobChild::InitializePrint sends a message to the parent\nprocess to ask it to initialize printing it spins the event loop and\nwaits for a reply.  If the parent fails to initialize printing it will\nsend back an error message followed immediately by a second message\ntelling the child process to delete its RemotePrintJobChild.  The error\nmessage causes the nested event loop to terminate and blocks\nRemotePrintJobChild::InitializePrint.  We then do various async things\nto clean up, some of which can try to post messages to the parent\nprocess's RemotePrintJobParent.  This is a problem since the delete\nmessage is pending in the child process's event loop resulting in a\nrace between the code that wants to use the RemotePrintJobChild to send\na message to the parent process, and the delete event that will make us\ncrash if anyone tries to use the RemotePrintJobChild.\n\nThis patch makes sure that if nsDeviceContextSpecProxy's BeginDocument\nreturns failure (remote print job initialization failed) that its\nEndDocument and AbortDocument methods are then no-ops and will not try\nto use its RemotePrintJobChild.  (BeginPage and EndPage are not changed\nsince they are not called if BeginDocument returns an error result.)\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2H6GHjngX7R", "files": ["widget/nsDeviceContextSpecProxy.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9002f06257c6ca8f58ec761f65a6ea0d90a35e25", "parents": ["04ec73c33ff12871343c7fe5dad3cc58c428a30a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1432409 part 2 - Make RemotePrintJobChild::OnStatusChange no-op if initialization failed. r=dholbert, a=lizzard\n\nAfter the part 1 fix, we can still (asynchronously) call some generic cleanup\ncode that tries to let the parent process's RemotePrintJobParent know that\nprinting failed under the stack:\n\n  RemotePrintJobChild::OnStatusChange\n  nsPrintData::DoOnStatusChange\n  nsPrintJob::FirePrintingErrorEvent\n  nsPrintJob::CleanupOnFailure\n\nWe crash on trying to use the RemotePrintJobChild to message the parent process\nsince the delete message from the parent has been processed.  This change makes\nRemotePrintJobChild::OnStatusChange check that it's initialized before trying\nto send any messages.\n\nPushing to CLOSED TREE since this passed a full Try build and is a topcrash\nwe want to land for beta ASAP.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FfizRMj2s2m", "files": ["layout/printing/ipc/RemotePrintJobChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0788981ad3266054b86bd77ef23ad8c8ec58825b", "parents": ["9002f06257c6ca8f58ec761f65a6ea0d90a35e25"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519170037, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "jwatt@jwatt.org"}, "8741": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\ncy -\u003e 4b8259c1f843", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64567978e14ea8332461f5133db4ebe2609d5c32", "parents": ["0788981ad3266054b86bd77ef23ad8c8ec58825b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\ncs -\u003e 58aef1c85dd2\ncy -\u003e 4b8259c1f843", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1717e9c3486ed8c7fe5514f34b837737164120cd", "parents": ["64567978e14ea8332461f5133db4ebe2609d5c32"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519179593, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8742": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nan -\u003e ac71e54ad75a\ncak -\u003e 0b556ac55063\ncs -\u003e 6226ef5779c4\nde -\u003e f4422ab9c36d\ndsb -\u003e 90672ff43813\nes-MX -\u003e 15523e5ccde9\nfr -\u003e f0db1a917045\nfy-NL -\u003e c5f51a1e7105\ngn -\u003e 8d86b6b54ad8", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14f49aef8e7a7dbe237bdc4a1d7bf053e783644e", "parents": ["1717e9c3486ed8c7fe5514f34b837737164120cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nach -\u003e 56fd9ee5caef\nan -\u003e 78a12453e28e\nar -\u003e 0d3c371d1534\nast -\u003e 6dd599fd7084\nbn-BD -\u003e ebc10eed174a\ncak -\u003e 0b556ac55063\nde -\u003e f4422ab9c36d\ndsb -\u003e 90672ff43813\nes-MX -\u003e 15523e5ccde9\nfr -\u003e d6abe328756d\nfy-NL -\u003e c5f51a1e7105\ngn -\u003e 52179878bc1c", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "49c87f84aa9c582768dc8412cdef0fd81e1a2090", "parents": ["14f49aef8e7a7dbe237bdc4a1d7bf053e783644e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519183224, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8743": {"changesets": [{"author": "philipp \u003cmadperson@gmx.at\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1043775 - Put old versions of GDATA GDKBFltDll64.dll on Dll blocklist. r=marco, a=RyanVM", "files": ["mozglue/build/WindowsDllBlocklist.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12759635b5dc0450dc32f43b345740363ac23fa1", "parents": ["49c87f84aa9c582768dc8412cdef0fd81e1a2090"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438274 - Fix browser and page actions clearance when navigating r=mixedpuppy a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Jb43H65LmFB", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/ext-browser.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_browserAction_context.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_pageAction_context.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_pageAction_title.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5709eb07da4ac8270ed98e1846766ecb48c35ab0", "parents": ["12759635b5dc0450dc32f43b345740363ac23fa1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437178 - Fix various pageAction visibiltiy issues when using show_matches and hide_matches r=mixedpuppy a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5jQ7MkkKWRk", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/ext-pageAction.js", "browser/components/extensions/schemas/page_action.json", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_pageAction_show_matches.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/schemas/manifest.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc4dc448c43bf76d945aa26742400aebb7115113", "parents": ["5709eb07da4ac8270ed98e1846766ecb48c35ab0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1437214 - if PathBuildingStep::Check fails due to a problem with the subject certificate rather than the potential issuer, set keepGoing to false r=jcj a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DEr4YgXfkOL", "files": ["security/pkix/lib/pkixbuild.cpp", "security/pkix/test/gtest/pkixbuild_tests.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "035e3c40f26ada3261445dc2b15d90ed26d78379", "parents": ["bc4dc448c43bf76d945aa26742400aebb7115113"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437741 - Part 1: Expect datachannel m-sections to be last. r=drno a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: At6HhsLsJQn", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/gtest/jsep_session_unittest.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b694e4a98fe2a5ffbe145fe490fab28c71fa46d", "parents": ["035e3c40f26ada3261445dc2b15d90ed26d78379"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437741 - Part 2: Map datachannel to an m-line after all RTP transceivers have been mapped. r=drno a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3hUvFaTYldx", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/jsep/JsepSessionImpl.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e683ed9cd7929ab3b838017c3ed0f127184474da", "parents": ["6b694e4a98fe2a5ffbe145fe490fab28c71fa46d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519208532, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "csabou@mozilla.com"}, "8744": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438559 - Add Ecosia for German Firefox. r=flod a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9ajRqAPlp0N", "files": ["browser/locales/search/list.json", "browser/locales/searchplugins/ecosia.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa4d6e4fb00cedc2d5b9772042e7d1c734e9745f", "parents": ["e683ed9cd7929ab3b838017c3ed0f127184474da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438645 - Prevent XDR from reading past its buffer. r=nbp a=lizzard\nWhile XDR data is supposed to be trusted, we currently run into a\ncorruption for some users/use-cases and so make more XDR operations\nfallible instead of crashing.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9FSLNWh9RxG", "files": ["js/src/jsatom.cpp", "js/src/vm/Xdr.cpp", "js/src/vm/Xdr.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2dba0b621fced66e0ac9c3dc48bbd216132e91b0", "parents": ["aa4d6e4fb00cedc2d5b9772042e7d1c734e9745f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438682 - 1. Cache initial selection offsets; r=esawin a=lizzard\n\nGetting the selection offsets in onCreateInputConnection can fail\nbecause of us being on a wrong thread. The solution is to cache the last\nselection offsets and use those in onCreateInputConnection.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AOlZsuOvzHm", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoInputConnection.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a753ffaee47ff482d0ccaabedb717ce351acbf4", "parents": ["2dba0b621fced66e0ac9c3dc48bbd216132e91b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438682 - 2. Implement dummy closeConnection; r=esawin a=lizzard\n\ncloseConnection is a new API introduced in N. We don't really support it\nat the moment but we also don't want the default behavior, so we\nimplement a dummy.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JY1Tl30X2s7", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoInputConnection.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f2ff6d6864feac244eb6892ec3b2deb8b397c65", "parents": ["9a753ffaee47ff482d0ccaabedb717ce351acbf4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519209026, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "8745": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429379, r=aswan,bz a=RyanVM", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/viewsource/nsViewSourceHandler.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/viewsource/nsViewSourceHandler.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27d0c44a5757ab9c686555b8e4e98c004b1b499d", "parents": ["2f2ff6d6864feac244eb6892ec3b2deb8b397c65"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Swan \u003caswan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1431371 Only grant activeTab to urls that match \u003call_urls\u003e r=kmag a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ApnAwGsIOaG", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/MatchPattern.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/MatchPattern.h", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "30b4121ee4c1e25332b9ad96dd992e8e38240b83", "parents": ["27d0c44a5757ab9c686555b8e4e98c004b1b499d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1435566: Make sure to drop frames for manual NAC from display: contents nodes. r=bz a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9CQIueSPwCV", "files": ["layout/base/nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "70bf6bd7b101725d99c35378c6acae21d9f217d7", "parents": ["30b4121ee4c1e25332b9ad96dd992e8e38240b83"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Rahm \u003cerahm@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1436768 - Avoid initializing LogModuleManager more than once. r=froydnj a=RyanVM\n\nThis adds some assertions to make the intended usage of LogModuleManager::Init\nmore clear.", "files": ["xpcom/base/Logging.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ea72bf995ee75e28f41c7f3e67ab79c0d9e810f", "parents": ["70bf6bd7b101725d99c35378c6acae21d9f217d7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1519217982, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8746": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1427957 - Bump security preload information expiration dates to 2018-06-26 for Firefox 59. r=jcj a=RyanVM", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53bb6f2559bd9360538766cafc1216bb248d8e58", "parents": ["2ea72bf995ee75e28f41c7f3e67ab79c0d9e810f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1388020. r=nical a=RyanVM", "files": ["gfx/layers/client/TextureClient.h", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/X11TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/d3d11/TextureD3D11.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/MacIOSurfaceTextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/TextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/tests/gtest/TestLayers.h", "gfx/tests/gtest/TestTextureCompatibility.cpp", "gfx/tests/gtest/TestTextures.cpp", "gfx/tests/gtest/TextureHelper.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d673d8e3429505ade45f412ac958448fff04f074", "parents": ["53bb6f2559bd9360538766cafc1216bb248d8e58"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1423528 - Recompute shadow visible rect for ContainerLayerMLGPU in case it has been changed by async animations. r=mstange a=RyanVM", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/ContainerLayerComposite.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/LayerManagerComposite.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/LayerManagerComposite.h", "gfx/layers/mlgpu/ContainerLayerMLGPU.cpp", "gfx/layers/mlgpu/ContainerLayerMLGPU.h", "gfx/layers/mlgpu/LayerMLGPU.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5463350d58a7bbfaa80ffa9dcd7004304c673e73", "parents": ["d673d8e3429505ade45f412ac958448fff04f074"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430856 - Cache CaptureCapability in CapabilityCandidate. r=jib a=lizzard\n\nThis will lead to less ipc calls, hopefully speeding up getUserMedia for many\ndevices.\n\nThis also lets us inject any hardcoded capabilities into the candidateSet in\nthe future (read: next patch).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HjIhRK1nVA1", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineCameraVideoSource.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineCameraVideoSource.h", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineRemoteVideoSource.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineRemoteVideoSource.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b398276a70a23ffa0e2d7e4b8396bdb665ed9542", "parents": ["5463350d58a7bbfaa80ffa9dcd7004304c673e73"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430856 - Default to two default capabilities when a camera can handle anything. r=jib a=lizzard\n\nIf a camera returns no capabilities we interpret it as it being able to handle\nany capability we throw at it. However, we also end up trying to start it with\nthe default capability of 0x0@0. This often works, but we can crash when\nrescaling it to the chosen target capability 0x0@0.\n\nWith this patch we inject up to two default capabilities, one at 640x480@30 and\none at 1280x720@30. With constraints present we'll try to adjust these defaults\nso they fit within the constraints while at the same time preserve the\naspect ratio given by prefs.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3mr7Li5TTbV", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineCameraVideoSource.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineCameraVideoSource.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2cc8275facbf5084a1be37b6bd9e503de133a141", "parents": ["b398276a70a23ffa0e2d7e4b8396bdb665ed9542"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1436468 - Send downloads to the correct directory. r=jlorenzo a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LSPNgFOjQhz", "files": ["taskcluster/docker/firefox-snap/snapcraft.yaml.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "75f5893a686fae9133324782ee4061647537e587", "parents": ["2cc8275facbf5084a1be37b6bd9e503de133a141"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437114 - ExternalHelperAppChild should send data to the parent actor in chunks, r=froydnj a=RyanVM", "files": ["uriloader/exthandler/ExternalHelperAppChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e0f32aa8b45d4f9b0280228c6caeeeece9739a4b", "parents": ["75f5893a686fae9133324782ee4061647537e587"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437760 P1 Propagate the FetchEvent.request.url fragment to the synthesized Response.url. r=asuth a=RyanVM", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0210188bd3aacb07cb298f4af4ca5e5be62cbd65", "parents": ["e0f32aa8b45d4f9b0280228c6caeeeece9739a4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437760 P2 Add a reftest that verifies svg images with fragment based targets renders properly when service workers intercept. r=xidorn a=RyanVM", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/images/colors.svg", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/resources/pass-through-worker.js", "testing/web-platform/tes